ents%20in%20Monday's%20motion%20to%20dismiss%20amount%20to%20this%3A%20SCOTUS%20lets%20me%20do%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20recent%20Supreme%20Court%20decision%20helps%20Adams%20by%20requiring%20a%20specific%20quid-pro-quo%20to%20prove%20bribery.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20first%20formal%20attack%20on%20last%20week's%20sweeping%20public%20corruption%20indictment%2C%20New%20York%20City%20Mayor%20Eric%20Adams%20takes%20aim%20at%20what%20his%20lawyer%20says%20is%20the%20weakest%20of%20the%20five%20federal%20charges%3A%20bribery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdams'%20argument%3F%20It's%20not%20bribery%20if%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20lets%20you%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20court%20filing%20on%20Monday%2C%20Adams%20attorney%20Alex%20Spiro%20cites%20a%20groundbreaking%20June%20SCOTUS%20decision%20as%20reason%20enough%20to%20toss%20the%20bribery%20count.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20is%20Snyder%20v.%20United%20States.%20It%20says%20handing%20a%20politician%20a%20bag%20of%20money%20is%20essentially%20A-OK%20under%20federal%20law%2C%20so%20long%20as%20there%20is%20no%20specifically%20stated%20quid-pro-quo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Adams'%20case%2C%20the%20Turkish%20officials%20who%20gave%20him%20%24100%2C000%20in%20upgraded%20flights%20and%20luxurious%20hotel%20stays%20never%20specifically%20linked%20those%20perks%20to%20a%20specific%20request%20for%20something%20in%20return%2C%20Spiro%20argues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20these%20were%20gratuities%2C%20not%20bribes%2C%20the%20lawyer%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20press%20conference%20after%20the%20motion%20was%20filed%2C%20Spiro%20compared%20Adams'%20%24100%2C000%20in%20flights%20and%20accommodations%20to%20perks%20like%20a%20hotel%20room%20upgrade%20or%20a%20good%20table%20at%20a%20restaurant%2C%20which%20are%20regularly%20extended%20to%20politicians.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20indictment%20does%20not%20sufficiently%20allege%20that%20Adams%20agreed%20to%20accept%20benefits%20in%20exchange%20for%20performing%20an%20official%20act%2C%26quot%3B%20Spiro%20wrote%20in%20Monday's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25178330-us-v-adams-mol-dismissal-20240930%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E25-page%20motion%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20the%20first%20time%20Snyder%20%E2%80%94%20a%20case%20named%20for%20an%20Indiana%20mayor%20who%20took%20%2413%2C000%20from%20a%20truck%20company%20%E2%80%94%20is%20being%20cited%20as%20a%20defense%20in%20a%20major%20public%20corruption%20prosecution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20makes%20perfect%20sense%20for%20Adams%20to%20cite%20it%2C%20said%20Michel%20Paradis%2C%20an%20attorney%20who%20teaches%20national%20security%20and%20constitutional%20law%20at%20Columbia%20Law%20School.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSnyder%20will%20be%20helpful%20to%20Adams%20principally%20in%20really%20putting%20the%20government%20to%20its%20proof%20on%20the%20quid-pro-quo%20elements%20of%20the%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20Paradis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFederal%20prosecutors%20say%20Adams%20enjoyed%20nearly%20a%20decade%20of%20globe-circling%20Turkish%20Airlines%20trips.%20They%20say%20that%20in%20return%2C%20Turkish%20officials%20asked%20for%20a%20few%20small%20favors%20from%20Adams%2C%20including%20that%20he%20not%20mention%20the%20Armenian%20genocide%2C%20and%20that%20he%20sever%20ties%20with%20a%20particular%20community%20center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20say%20Turkey%20asked%20Adams%20for%20a%20large%20favor%2C%20one%20that%20Adams%20granted%3A%20in%202021%2C%20the%20then-leading%20mayoral%20candidate%20leaned%20on%20city%20fire%20officials%20to%20bend%20the%20rules%20and%20approve%20occupancy%20for%20a%20Midtown%20skyscraper%20that%20held%20the%20Turkish%20consulate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20indictment%20quotes%20an%20unnamed%20Turkish%20official%20telling%20an%20Adams%20staffer%20that%20because%20Turkey%20had%20supported%20the%20soon-to-be%20mayor%2C%20it%20was%20now%20%26quot%3Bhis%20turn%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20Adams'%20%E2%80%94%20to%20support%20Turkey%20by%20getting%20the%20consulate%20opened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20feds%20say%20Adams%20responded%20when%20told%20by%20the%20staffer%20that%20Turkey%20saw%20this%20as%20%26quot%3Bhis%20turn%26quot%3B%20to%20reciprocate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpiro%20says%20in%20his%20filing%20that%20the%20travel%20perks%20Adams%20enjoyed%20are%20the%20kind%20of%20gifts%20that%20constituents%20or%20foreign%20dignitaries%20routinely%20give%2C%20to%20show%20their%20appreciation%20or%20gain%20access%20to%20a%20politician.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESnyder%20%E2%80%94%20in%20a%20majority%20opinion%20written%20by%20Justice%20Brett%20Kavanaugh%20and%20joined%20by%20the%20current%20conservative%20supermajority's%20five%20other%20justices%20%E2%80%94%20broadens%20the%20definition%20of%20%26quot%3Bgratuities%26quot%3B%20and%20limits%20the%20definition%20of%20%26quot%3Bbribes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(In%20addition%20to%20Spiro%2C%20Adams%20is%20represented%20by%20Avi%20Perry%20and%20William%20Burck.%20Burck%20is%20on%20the%20board%20of%20Fox%20Corp%2C%20clerked%20for%20Anthony%20Kennedy%2C%20and%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2018%2F09%2F02%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fwilliam-burck.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20a%20friend%20of%20Kavanaugh.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20new%2C%20post-Snyder%20world%2C%20the%20feds%20must%20prove%20that%20a%20politician%20clearly%20knew%20that%20cash%20or%20goods%20are%20being%20offered%20as%20payment%20for%20an%20official%20act%2C%20and%20that%20the%20official%20act%20was%20taken%20specifically%20in%20response%20to%20that%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECritics%20of%20the%20SCOTUS%20ruling%20feared%20it%20would%20open%20the%20door%20to%20politicians%20freely%20taking%20handouts.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAdams%20will%20argue%20that%20the%20Turkish%20government%20gave%20him%20things%20out%20of%20gratitude%20for%20his%20past%20friendliness%20toward%20Turkey's%20interests%2C%26quot%3B%20merely%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bthank%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Paradis%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20government%20will%20argue%20that%20Turkey%20gave%20him%20goodies%2C%20and%20he%20accepted%20those%20goodies%2C%20on%20the%20understanding%20that%20he%20would%20continue%20to%20use%20his%20political%20position%20for%20Turkey's%20benefit%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20constitutional%20law%20expert%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPrior%20to%20Snyder%2C%20the%20government%20would%20not%20have%20had%20to%20show%20such%20a%20tight%20connection%20between%20the%20bribes%20and%20the%20expectation%20that%20Adams%20would%20do%20things%20for%20them%20in%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20Paradis%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%20they%20do%2C%20which%20is%20why%20the%20indictment%20puts%20a%20lot%20of%20emphasis%20on%20the%20consulate%20and%20the%20Armenian%20genocide%20allegations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFederal%20prosecutors%20have%20yet%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20motion%20to%20dismiss.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Justice%20Department%20and%20Spiro%20didn't%20immediately%20return%20requests%20for%20comment%20for%20this%20story%20Monday%20afternoon.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdams%20has%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%20to%20the%20indictment%2C%20which%20also%20charges%20him%20with%20illegally%20accepting%20campaign%20contributions%20from%20Turkish%20officials%20and%20others%20via%20straw%20donors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20convicted%20on%20all%20counts%2C%20he%20faces%20a%20maximum%20of%2045%20years%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feric-adams-scotus-thank-challenges-bribery-charge-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727731620000%2C%22visual%22%3A