ng%20search%20operations.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F56-years-after-air-force-plane-crash-over-rohtang-pass-4-more-bodies-found-6687015%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hydra%20Trading%20sells%201.24%25%20stake%20in%20RBL%20Bank%20for%20Rs%20152%20crore%20in%20open%20market%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727717098000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2024-09%2F04%2Fthumb%2Ffitandfill%2F400X400%2F1725434568-0402.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fhydra-trading-sells-1-24-stake-in-rbl-bank-for-rs-152-crore-in-open-market-124093001371_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20block%20deal%20data%20available%20on%20the%20BSE%2C%20Hydra%20Trading%20Pvt%20Ltd%20offloaded%2075.11%20lakh%20shares%20or%201.24%20per%20cent%20stake%20in%20RBL%20Bank%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fhydra-trading-sells-1-24-stake-in-rbl-bank-for-rs-152-crore-in-open-market-124093001371_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fhydra-trading-sells-1-24-stake-in-rbl-bank-for-rs-152-crore-in-open-market-124093001371_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fhydra-trading-sells-1-24-stake-in-rbl-bank-for-rs-152-crore-in-open-market-124093001371_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Scientists%20Explain%20Mount%20Everest's%20'More%20Than%20Expected'%20Growth%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMount%20Everest%20is%20Earth's%20tallest%20mountain%20-%20towering%205.5%20miles%20(8.85%20km)%20above%20sea%20level%20-%20and%20is%20still%20growing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20Himalayas%20are%20continuing%20an%20inexorable%20uplift%20that%20dates%20back%20to%20their%20birth%20roughly%2050%20million%20years%20ago%20when%20the%20Indian%20subcontinent%20collided%20with%20Eurasia%2C%20Everest%20is%20growing%20more%20than%20expected%20from%20this%20alone.%20Scientists%20now%20think%20they%20know%20the%20reason%20why%2C%20and%20it%20has%20to%20do%20with%20the%20monumental%20merger%20of%20two%20nearby%20river%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEverest%20has%20gained%20roughly%2049-164%20feet%20(15-50%20meters)%20in%20height%20due%20to%20this%20change%20in%20the%20regional%20river%20system%2C%20with%20the%20Kosi%20river%20merging%20with%20the%20Arun%20river%20approximately%2089%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20researchers%20estimated.%20That%20translates%20to%20an%20uplift%20rate%20of%20roughly%200.01-0.02%20inches%20(0.2-0.5%20millimetres)%20per%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20geological%20process%20at%20work%2C%20they%20said%2C%20is%20called%20isostatic%20rebound.%20It%20involves%20the%20rise%20of%20land%20masses%20on%20Earth's%20crust%20when%20the%20weight%20of%20the%20surface%20diminishes.%20The%20crust%2C%20Earth's%20outermost%20layer%2C%20essentially%20floats%20atop%20a%20mantle%20layer%20made%20of%20hot%2C%20semi-liquid%20rock.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20case%2C%20the%20merger%20of%20the%20rivers%20-%20more%20like%20a%20hostile%20takeover%2C%20with%20the%20Kosi%20subjugating%20the%20Arun%20as%20the%20rivers%20changed%20course%20over%20time%20-%20resulted%20in%20accelerated%20erosion%20that%20has%20carried%20off%20huge%20amounts%20of%20rock%20and%20soil%2C%20reducing%20the%20weight%20of%20the%20region%20near%20Everest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIsostatic%20rebound%20can%20be%20likened%20to%20a%20floating%20object%20adjusting%20its%20position%20when%20weight%20is%20removed%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20geoscientist%20Jin-Gen%20Dai%20of%20China%20University%20of%20Geosciences%20in%20Beijing%2C%20one%20of%20the%20leaders%20of%20the%20study%20published%20on%20Monday%20in%20the%20journal%20Nature%20Geoscience.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20a%20heavy%20load%2C%20such%20as%20ice%20or%20eroded%20rock%2C%20is%20removed%20from%20the%20Earth's%20crust%2C%20the%20land%20beneath%20slowly%20rises%20in%20response%2C%20much%20like%20a%20boat%20rising%20in%20water%20when%20cargo%20is%20unloaded%2C%26quot%3B%20Dai%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20gorge%20of%20the%20merged%20river%20system%20is%20located%20approximately%2028%20miles%20(45%20km)%20east%20of%20Everest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%2C%20who%20used%20numerical%20models%20to%20simulate%20the%20evolution%20of%20the%20river%20system%2C%20estimated%20that%20isostatic%20rebound%20accounts%20for%20about%2010%25%20of%20Everest's%20annual%20uplift%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20geological%20process%20is%20not%20unique%20to%20the%20Himalayas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20classic%20example%20is%20in%20Scandinavia%2C%20where%20the%20land%20is%20still%20rising%20in%20response%20to%20the%20melting%20of%20thick%20ice%20sheets%20that%20covered%20the%20region%20during%20the%20last%20Ice%20Age.%20This%20process%20continues%20today%2C%20affecting%20coastlines%20and%20landscapes%2C%20thousands%20of%20years%20after%20the%20ice%20retreated%2C%26quot%3B%20Dai%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStudy%20co-author%20Adam%20Smith%2C%20a%20University%20College%20London%20doctoral%20student%20in%20Earth%20sciences%2C%20said%20GPS%20measurements%20reveal%20the%20continued%20rising%20of%20Everest%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20Himalayas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20uplift%20outpaces%20the%20continued%20surface%20erosion%20caused%20by%20factors%20such%20as%20wind%2C%20rain%20and%20river%20flow.%20As%20this%20erosion%20continues%2C%20Everest's%20uplift%20rate%20from%20isostatic%20rebound%20may%20increase%2C%20Smith%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeighbouring%20peaks%20including%20Lhotse%2C%20the%20world's%20fourth%20highest%2C%20and%20Makalu%2C%20the%20fifth%20highest%2C%20also%20get%20a%20boost%20from%20the%20same%20process.%20Lhotse%20is%20experiencing%20an%20uplift%20rate%20similar%20to%20Everest.%20Makalu%2C%20situated%20closer%20to%20the%20Arun%2C%20has%20a%20slightly%20higher%20uplift%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20research%20underscores%20our%20planet's%20dynamic%20nature.%20Even%20a%20seemingly%20immutable%20feature%20like%20Mount%20Everest%20is%20subject%20to%20ongoing%20geological%20processes%2C%20reminding%20us%20that%20Earth%20is%20constantly%20changing%2C%20often%20in%20ways%20imperceptible%20in%20our%20daily%20lives%2C%26quot%3B%20Dai%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarth's%20rigid%20outer%20part%20is%20divided%20into%20colossal%20plates%20that%20move%20gradually%20over%20time%20in%20a%20process%20called%20plate%20tectonics%2C%20with%20the%20Himalayas%20rising%20following%20a%20collision%20between%20two%20plates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEverest%2C%20also%20called%20Sagarmatha%20in%20Nepali%20and%20Chomolungma%20in%20Tibetan%2C%20is%20situated%20on%20the%20border%20between%20Nepal%20and%20the%20Tibet%20Autonomous%20Region%20of%20China.%20It%20was%20named%20for%20George%20Everest%2C%20a%2019th-century%20British%20surveyor%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMount%20Everest%20occupies%20a%20unique%20place%20in%20human%20consciousness%2C%26quot%3B%20Dai%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPhysically%2C%20it%20represents%20Earth's%20highest%20point%2C%20giving%20it%20immense%20significance%20simply%20by%20virtue%20of%20its%20stature%2C%26quot%3B%20Dai%20added.%20%26quot%3BCulturally%2C%20Everest%20is%20sacred%20to%20local%20Sherpa%20and%20Tibetan%20communities.%20Globally%2C%20it%20symbolizes%20the%20ultimate%20challenge%2C%20embodying%20human%20endurance%20and%20our%20drive%20to%20surpass%20perceived%20limits.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20fro